race.comment: SUMMER'S LEGACY (10) landed just off the speed last start and bolted in over 1650m at Belmont last time out. Up to 1800m now is a good move, though the wide draw is a niggle. Trust Pike to get it right though and if she can improve again out in trip she'll be hard to hold out. MAJOR MARIO (9) missed narrowly in a similar race last start over this course and distance, finishing 0.6L away. He maps for a similar run this time around and he rates highly on his recent effort. Can make his presence felt once again. MISSISSIPPI DAWN (15) disappointed over this track and trip as an equal fave here last start after a strong effort here two back. Likely to get back from the draw once again, but she's better than she showed last start and improvement is on the cards. I'M CRAFTY (3) is racing well and his form ties in through SUMMER'S LEGACY. Worth including. I'M NIPOTE (5) is racing in good order and is not to be discounted.
